The paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation, which is a problem commonly studied in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves aligning class-level distributions and learning the classifier in the target domain, which are also relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM).
